# Design reference — visual and structural guide

Generated HTML/React screens live in the sibling folder `../workflowHub-design-reference/`.
Use them **only as a visual and structural reference** when building Angular screens.

## Rules

- **Never** import, copy-paste, or ship reference code into the Angular app.
- Re-express layouts in Angular idioms: standalone components, Tailwind, PrimeNG, SCSS tokens.
- Match structure, spacing, typography, and interaction patterns from the reference.
- Implement under `frontend/src/app/features/<area>/` per ai-rules folder-structure rules.
- Pointer doc: `design-reference/README.md` in this repo.

## Key reference files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `Workflow Hub.html` | Full-page layout overview |
| `app.jsx` / `app.css` | App shell and global styles |
| `colors_and_type.css` | Color and typography tokens |
| `ui.jsx` | Reusable UI primitives |
| `screens*.jsx` | Individual screen layouts |

When the reference and PRD conflict, follow the PRD and coordinate with design.
